[![Download Options][1]][1]

For testing purposes, I tried this code but it doesn&#39;t work:

```
(function() {
    var _old_confirm = window.confirm;
    window.confirm = function() {
                     // run some code when the confirm pops up
        document.body.innerHTML += &quot;&lt;br&gt;confirming&quot;;
        _old_confirm.apply(window,arguments);
                     // run some code after the confirm
        document.body.innerHTML += &quot;&lt;br&gt;done confirming&lt;br&gt;&quot;;
    };
})();
```


  [1]: https://i.stack.imgur.com/xYtoE.png

answers.body_markdown:
&gt; But I want the yellow background to be adapted to the text, not 100%

You can wrap your `Text` element with a `View`, and then put a dummy `Text` element next to your `Text` to cover the remaining empty space.

Like so:

    &lt;View style={styles.container}&gt;
        &lt;Text style={styles.yourText}&gt;
          Sexualit&#233; et pr&#233;vention
        &lt;/Text&gt;
        &lt;Text style={styles.textDummy}/&gt;
    &lt;/View&gt;

CSS:

      container: {
       flexDirection:&quot;row&quot;,
      },
      yourText: {
        backgroundColor:&quot;yellow&quot;
      },
      textDummy: {
        flexGrow:1
      }

Here is the result:

[![enter image description here][1]][1]


----------

As a second solution you can add just  

     alignSelf: &quot;baseline&quot;

to your `title`. Like this:

     title: {
            backgroundColor: &#39;yellow&#39;
            borderWidth: 1,
            borderRadius: 2.5,
            marginBottom: 5,
            padding: 5,
            alignSelf:&quot;baseline&quot;
        }

  [1]: https://i.stack.imgur.com/oOinh.png

